Subject: Application for Change of Status from H-1B to F-1

Dear Sir/Madam,

I am writing to respectfully request a change of status from H-1B to F-1. I am currently employed by [Your Employer's Name], and my H-1B status is valid until [H-1B Expiration Date]. However, I have been accepted into [Name of University] to pursue [Name of Degree Program], and I believe that continuing my education will significantly contribute to my professional growth and future career opportunities.

I have enclosed the following documents to support my application:
1. Form I-539, Application to Extend/Change Nonimmigrant Status
2. Form I-20, Certificate of Eligibility for Nonimmigrant Student Status, issued by [Name of University]
3. Proof of SEVIS fee payment
4. Letter of admission from [Name of University]
5. Copies of my current and previous H-1B approval notices
6. Copies of my current and previous I-94 records
7. Copies of my passport and visa pages
8. Evidence of financial support (bank statements, scholarship letter, etc.)
9. A detailed explanation of my intent to study and future plans

I am fully aware of the responsibilities and requirements associated with F-1 status and am prepared to comply with all regulations. I am committed to maintaining my full-time student status and adhering to the guidelines set forth by the Department of Homeland Security.

Thank you for considering my application. I am confident that my pursuit of further education will allow me to gain valuable knowledge and skills that will enhance my professional qualifications. I respectfully request your approval for this change of status to enable me to achieve these goals.

Should you require any additional information or documentation, please do not hesitate to contact me at [Your Phone Number] or [Your Email Address].

Sincerely,

[Your Name]  
[Signature (if submitting by mail)]  

Enclosures:  
- Form I-539  
- Form I-20  
- Proof of SEVIS fee payment  
- Admission letter  
- H-1B approval notices  
- I-94 records  
- Passport and visa copies  
